# ğŸŒ¿ Xenium Data Analysis Training

Welcome to the **Xenium Data Analysis Training Course**!  
This 4-week program introduces the fundamentals of analyzing **10x Genomics Xenium in situ** transcriptomics data using **R** and **Xenium Explorer**.

The course is designed for new researchers and PhD students to gain hands-on experience with Xenium data â€” from loading raw output to visualizing gene expression, clustering cells, and identifying marker genes.

---

## ğŸ“˜ Course Overview

**Instructor:** Dr. Min-Yao Jhu  
**Duration:** 4 weeks (1-hour guided session + ~3 days of independent practice per week)  
**Tools:** R (Seurat v5, Xenium Ranger) and Xenium Explorer  
**Prerequisites:** Basic R and single-cell analysis experience  

---

## ğŸ¯ Learning Objectives

By the end of the course, you will be able to:

1. Understand the structure and components of Xenium output files  
2. Load Xenium data into R using Seurat functions  
3. Visualize spatial gene expression using R and Xenium Explorer  
4. Perform clustering and dimensionality reduction  
5. Detect and interpret marker genes for specific spatial domains  

---

## ğŸ—“ï¸ Weekly Syllabus

### **Week 1 â€“ Data Overview & Loading**
- Understand Xenium output (`cells.csv.gz`, `transcripts.csv.gz`, `metadata.json`, `morphology.ome.tif`)
- Load data into R using `LoadXenium()`
- Perform basic quality control and explore metadata  
â¡ï¸ [Go to Week 1 Lesson](/Xenium_data_analysis_training/week1_data_overview/lesson.md)

---

### **Week 2 â€“ Visualization & Exploration**
- Use `SpatialFeaturePlot()` to visualize spatial expression patterns  
- Explore the dataset in **Xenium Explorer**  
- Export publication-quality figures  
â¡ï¸ [Go to Week 2 Lesson](../week2_visualization/lesson.md)

---

### **Week 3 â€“ Clustering & Dimension Reduction**
- Normalize data with `SCTransform()`  
- Run PCA and UMAP  
- Identify clusters and visualize them spatially  
â¡ï¸ [Go to Week 3 Lesson](../week3_clustering/lesson.md)

---

### **Week 4 â€“ Marker Detection & Interpretation**
- Identify cluster-specific marker genes using `FindAllMarkers()`  
- Visualize expression using `FeaturePlot()` and `DotPlot()`  
- Interpret biological meaning of clusters  
â¡ï¸ [Go to Week 4 Lesson](../week4_markers/lesson.md)

